##! Please refer to the documentation at
##! https://coreruleset.org/docs/development/regex_assembly/.

##! Bash - Tilde Expansion
##! Detects the following patterns which are common in Unix shell scripts and one-liners

##! Require start-of-string or shell boundary before tilde to reduce FPs
##! on values like "cookie=abc~+1" while preserving detection of
##! shell-chained commands like "cmd;~+1", "cmd|~+1", "$(~+1)"

##!^ (?:^|[\s;|&`$(<>])

~\+$
~\+\d+
~-$
~-\d+
